### Enable Askama Opt-in Features

Source: https://askama.readthedocs.io/en/stable/print

Shows how to enable opt-in features in Askama by specifying them in the `features` array in the `Cargo.toml` file. This reduces dependencies and compilation time.

```TOML
[dependencies]
askama = { version = "0.14.0", features = ["serde_json"] }

```

--------------------------------

### Opt-in to Serde JSON Filter

Source: https://askama.readthedocs.io/en/stable/features

This snippet demonstrates how to enable the `|json` filter in Askama by opting into the `serde_json` feature in your Cargo.toml file. This is useful when you need to serialize data to JSON within your templates.

```toml
[dependencies]
askama = { version = "0.14.0", features = ["serde_json"] }
```

--------------------------------

### Askama Web Framework Integration

Source: https://askama.readthedocs.io/en/stable/print

Examples and guidance on integrating Askama with various Rust web frameworks, including Actix-Web, Axum, Poem, Rocket, Salvo, and Warp.

```rust
Actix-Web
Axum
Poem
Rocket
Salvo
Warp
```

--------------------------------

### Axum HTML Response

Source: https://askama.readthedocs.io/en/stable/frameworks

Shows how to return an Askama template as an HTML response using Axum's `Html` type.

```rust
use axum::response::{Html, IntoResponse};

async fn handler() -> Result<impl IntoResponse, AppError> {
    …
    Ok(Html(template.render()?))
}
```

--------------------------------

### Axum Custom Error Handling

Source: https://askama.readthedocs.io/en/stable/print

Illustrates how to implement a custom error type for Axum applications using Askama. It details the implementation of the `IntoResponse` trait for custom error types to manage Askama rendering errors and produce appropriate responses.

```rust
use axum::response::IntoResponse;
use askama::Template;

#[derive(Debug, displaydoc::Display, thiserror::Error)]
enum AppError {
    /// could not render template
    Render(#[from] askama::Error),
}

impl IntoResponse for AppError {
    fn into_response(self) -> Response {
        #[derive(Debug, Template)]
        #[template(path = "error.html")]
        struct Tmpl { … }

        let status = match &self {
            AppError::Render(_) => StatusCode::INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR,
        };
        let tmpl = Tmpl { … };
        if let Ok(body) = tmpl.render() {
            (status, Html(body)).into_response()
        } else {
            (status, "Something went wrong").into_response()
        }
    }
}
```

